<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crowd Cheers at Brett's Speech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- They cheered. They laughed. They wiped  
away tears. 
</P>
<P>
	But mostly they cheered.  
</P>
<P>
	Watching George Brett's Hall of Fame acceptance speech on the  
huge Jumbotron at Kauffman Stadium Sunday proved as thrilling for 
Kansas City fans as all the clutch hits and heroic plays he made 
during his memorable 21-year career. 
</P>
<P>
	``I started watching George when I was 13. I grew up watching  
him and now my sons are George Brett fans, too,'' said Howard Cline 
of Kansas City, Mo. ``I think he's the greatest ballplayer of his 
day. And now everybody in the world knows he's one of the greatest 
of all time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the crowd of 21,000 who sweated through 100-degree heat  
watching the Royals rally to beat Oakland 13-11 in 10 innings stuck 
around to watch a tape of his speech, which had actually taken 
place during the sixth inning when the home team trailed 11-5. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll never forget that 1980 season when he hit .390,'' said  
Tom Flaherty, who drove down from Omaha, Neb., just to watch Brett 
several times a year. ``That was the greatest season I ever saw any 
ballplayer have.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In his speech, Brett was careful to thank almost everyone who  
had a hand in his career, and the crowd applauded at the sound of 
almost every familiar name. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hal McRae would do whatever it took to win a game,'' Brett  
said. Big applause. 
</P>
<P>
	Then an even bigger cheer went up when Brett mentioned the late  
Dick Howser, who managed the Royals to the 1985 World Series title, 
and Whitey Herzog, who took them to three straight AL West 
championships from 1976-78. 
</P>
<P>
	``Whitey said, `George, you're going to play third and hit third  
every day I'm managing,''' Brett said as the fans applauded. 
</P>
<P>
	When he thanked his mother for all she'd done and said in a  
choking voice, ``I love you,'' Jan Cook of Lee's Summit, Mo., had 
tears running down her cheeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think that's so sweet. But that's just like George,'' she  
said. ``I think it was just beautiful the way he thanked his family 
and all his teammates and everything. We were really lucky to have 
George.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When George said how lucky he was to have Kansas City, the crowd  
really cut loose. 
</P>
<P>
	``You welcomed me into your beautiful city and into your  
homes,'' Brett said. ``And to this day I am so proud to call Kansas 
City home. I have so many things to be thankful for and you made it 
possible for me. Thank you.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Thank you, George. Thank you,'' several fans shouted.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
