<HEADLINE> Mets, Yankees Series Draws 300,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Yankees and New York Mets, who  
rarely are home at the same time, drew more than 300,000 for six 
games this weekend and won them all. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees drew 54,944 for Sunday's series finale against the  
Cleveland Indians for a three-game total of 162,518 at Yankee 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mets drew 47,679 against the Chicago Cubs on Sunday night,  
raising their series total at Shea Stadium to 147,809. 
</P>
<P>
	In all, the six games drew 310,327.  
  	   	
