<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Limb Snaps From Tree, Kills Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAY VILLAGE, Ohio (AP) -- A large tree limb fell about 35 feet  
onto a table and killed three people attending a backyard picnic, 
police and firefighters said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear what caused the limb to snap around 9 p.m.  
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was not raining and there was no thunder, but there was  
some wind,'' Police Chief David Wright said. 
</P>
<P>
	The National Weather Service said 40 mph winds were reported  
about 7 p.m., but no strong winds were reported at the time of the 
accident in the suburb west of Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	The tree limb, about 1 1/2 feet to 2 feet in diameter and 35 feet  
long, was so large four men couldn't lift it, said Timothy 
McDonough, who lives on an adjacent street and was walking by when 
he heard the limb crash. 
</P>
<P>
	A 46-year-old woman died at the scene, a 30-year-old man died en  
route to St. John West Shore Hospital and a 32-year-old man died 
shortly after arriving at Lakewood hospital, police and nursing 
supervisors said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
