<HEADLINE> Galaxy 2, Wizards 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Clint Mathis and Ezra Hendrickson scored  
21 minutes apart as the Los Angeles Galaxy edged the Kansas City 
Wizards 2-1 on Sunday at the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
	Mathis scored 22 seconds into the match -- the fourth-fastest  
goal in Major League Soccer history -- and Hendrickson followed with 
a goal 21 minutes later to give the Galaxy a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 35th minute, Alex Bunbury pulled the Wizards within 2-1  
when his shot from the penalty area bounced off the hands of Los 
Angeles goalkeeper Kevin Hartman and into the goal. It was 
Bunbury's third goal in six games. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards had three strong chances to tie the score in the  
final 12 minutes. Shots by Bunbury and Chris Klein hit the crossbar 
in the 78th and 86th minutes, respectively, and a free kick by 
Preki in the 80th minute sailed just wide of the right goal post. 
</P>
<P>
	Hartman made one save as the Galaxy won for the sixth time in  
seven matches, moving within a point of Chicago and Dallas for 
second place in the Western Conference. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
