<HEADLINE> Piniella, Segui Ejected From Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Seattle manager Lou Piniella was ejected in  
the fifth inning of Sunday's game at Minnesota for arguing an 
appeal call by third-base umpire Durwood Merril. 
</P>
<P>
	One inning later, Mariners first baseman David Segui was tossed  
by home plate ump Mike Everitt. Segui had been brushed back by 
Twins pitcher Brad Radke before flying out and was ejected for 
yelling at Everitt after returning to the Seattle bench. 
</P>
<P>
	Piniella was tossed after throwing his cap while arguing that  
Raul Ibanez had not left third base early on an apparent sacrifice 
fly by Ken Griffey. 
</P>
<P>
	With Seattle already ahead 4-0, Ibanez appeared to have scored  
from third on Griffey's sacrifice fly. But Minnesota appealed the 
play and Merril made the out call for an inning-ending double play. 
</P>
<P>
	In his anger, Piniella attempted to lift up third base but  
couldn't, so he kicked dirt on the base instead. When he returned 
to the dugout, he threw several bats onto the playing field. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first time Piniella has been ejected this season. The  
Mariners had lost three straight and 11 of their past 18 entering 
the game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
