<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Photos Upset 'Dawson's Creek' Star </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Michelle Williams has appeared on stage totally  
naked and has been on her own since age 15. On top of that, she 
plays a bad girl on ``Dawson's Creek.'' Still, when the teen-age 
actress saw a sexy photo of her on a magazine cover, she was 
horrified. 
</P>
<P>
	``Those pictures are not me,'' Williams says in Sunday's Daily  
News, referring to the cover shot and other photos in Maxim 
magazine. ``You should see me in flannel pajamas and greasy hair. 
</P>
<P>
	``It upsets me to see those pictures. I hate the fact that the  
girls who watch `Dawson's Creek' will see them. I have a 
15-year-old sister. I don't want to be an unhealthy role model. I 
don't want to see girls like me trivialized and sexualized.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Williams, 18, moved to Los Angeles from San Diego -- alone -- to  
pursue her acting career, having graduated from high school at age 
15. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had the `from-birth-to-16-year-old' blues. It was a  
perpetual mood in my life,'' she said. ``So I moved out. I don't 
know if I was ready, but I was determined.'' 
  	   	
</P>
