and pines burned within one-half mile of a major highway and sent a 
large column of smoke billowing in the sky Saturday just east of 
Reno. Other fires had blackened 32,000 acres in the state's 
northeast corner and 17,000 acres near Naval Air Station Fallon. A 
blaze in California had spread across 13,700 acres. 

