	Vote Worries Venezuela Opposition  
</P>
<P>
	CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) -- Once members of a powerful  
constitutional assembly are elected, Venezuelan President Hugo 
Chavez says they will usher in democratic change. But with the 
former coup leader urging the assembly to abolish both Congress and 
the Supreme Court, opposition leaders fear today's vote is a 
prelude to dictatorship. Chavez proposed the assembly to break a 
domination of politics by traditional parties that he says has 
impoverished Venezuela and turned it into one of the world's most 
corrupt countries. 

</P>
