	Tree Limb Snaps, Three Die  
</P>
<P>
	BAY VILLAGE, Ohio (AP) -- A large tree limb fell about 35 feet  
onto a table and killed three people attending a backyard picnic 
last night, police and firefighters said. It was unclear what 
caused the limb to snap. The National Weather Service said 40 mph 
winds were reported about 7 p.m., but no strong winds were reported 
at the time of the accident in the suburb west of Cleveland. The 
tree limb, about 1 1/2 feet to 2 feet in diameter and 35 feet long, 
was so large four men couldn't lift it. 

</P>
