<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McNabb Absent as Eagles Open Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Donovan McNabb, the No. 2 draft pick  
expected to lead the Philadelphia Eagles out of one of the team's 
darkest eras, was absent and unsigned Sunday as rookies reported 
for training camp. 
</P>
<P>
	McNabb did not join first-year players and selected veterans at  
a team meeting Sunday night. First-year coach Andy Reid said McNabb 
and other unsigned players would be fined if they missed any 
practice time. 
</P>
<P>
	It marked the first time the Eagles had unsigned rookies at the  
start of camp since Jeffrey Lurie bought the team in 1994. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will not allow the signings to be a distraction,'' said  
Reid, hired to replace Ray Rhodes after Philadelphia went 3-13 last 
season. ``We will go forth with those players that are on hand.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Eagles also signed second-round pick Barry Gardner to a  
five-year deal, fourth-round pick John Wellbourne to a three-year 
deal, and sixth-round pick Cecil Martin to a three-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Four draft picks remained unsigned when Reid convened his first  
official meeting as coach Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Reid expected about 30 players on the field Monday morning for  
practice, but didn't know when McNabb or the other unsigned rookies 
would report. 
</P>
<P>
	``It doesn't matter whether it's Donovan or whomever,'' Reid  
said. ``Any time a player misses a practice, it's a problem. I've 
talked to you about the quarterback position before. That's an 
important position. It doesn't help his progress.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McNabb is listed as the backup quarterback to Doug Pederson, a  
31-year-old career third-stringer whom Reid has picked as the 
starter. 
</P>
<P>
	McNabb's agent, Fletcher Smith, and Eagles executive vice  
president Joe Banner have said that voidable years and a buyback 
clause are the sticking points in negotiations. The Eagles don't 
want voidable years, while Smith is looking to include them after 
three or four seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith is believed to be considering a seven-year offer worth  
about $50 million, including a signing bonus of up to $12 million. 
Reid talked with Banner Sunday and characterized negotiations as 
``productive.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Both sides want this to work,'' Reid said. ``They're going to  
exhaust the ends here to make this happen.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Banner characterized the contract as about 60 percent finished.  
Still, he acknowledged that McNabb would miss practice time even if 
he signed late Sunday night. McNabb's contract will be 20-30 pages 
long when it's finished. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm optimistic, but I don't want to give the impression that I  
think it's imminent,'' Banner said. 
</P>
<P>
	McNabb's absence placed added pressure on Pederson, a free agent  
from Green Bay who showed up on time at the team's training 
facility at Lehigh University. Veterans report to camp on 
Wednesday, and the team holds its first full-squad workout with 
Reid as coach on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Rookies hold their first workout Monday morning with or without  
McNabb, the former Syracuse quarterback picked after the Cleveland 
Browns chose Tim Couch. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
