<HEADLINE> Tampa Bay 3, Colorado Rapids 2 (SO) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        DENVER (AP) -- Josh Keller scored the game-winning goal as  
the Tampa Bay Mutiny outscored the Colorado Rapids 3-2 in a shootout 
Sunday to take a 3-2 decision over the Colorado Rapids. 
</P>
<P>
        Keller beat Rapids goalkeeper Ian Feuer with a quick shot to  
the left before Mutiny goalkeeper Scott Garlick sealed the victory 
with a save on Chris Martinez's sixth-round attempt. 
</P>
<P>
        Mauricio Ramos scored in the 31st minute and Raul Diaz Arce  
in the 59th minute of regulation for Tampa Bay. Anders Limpar scored 
in the 15th minute and Darren Sawatzky tied it in the 78th minute for 
Colorado, which outshot the Mutiny 23-9. 
  	   	
