<HEADLINE> Soccer Player Dies During Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) -- An up-and-coming Romanian soccer  
player died of a heart attack while playing a match in the capital, 
local media reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Shortly after entering the game Saturday, midfielder Stefan  
Vrabioru, 24, collapsed on the field and was taken to the hospital. 
An hour later, he was pronounced dead of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
	Vrabioru's coach, Vasile Simionas, said the player had no  
history of health problems, the Mediafax news agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	Vrabioru played for Astra Ploiesti, based in the city of  
Ploiesti, 37 miles north of Bucharest. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
