<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> United 2, Revolution 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Roy Lassiter and Cary Talley scored to  
give depleted DC United a 2-0 victory Sunday over the New England 
Revolution. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory improves the Eastern Conference-leading United to  
13-7, seven points ahead of Columbus. 
</P>
<P>
	DC, missing seven starters due to international duty or injury,  
opened the scoring in the 11th minute through Lassiter, who headed 
in a short lob by Clint Peay on the left side, beating Walter Zenga 
from nine yards along the left post. Lassiter, MLS's leading 
goalscorer, now has 15 goals. 
</P>
<P>
	United added to its lead in the 33rd minute when Talley scored  
off an Antonio Otero corner kick on the left side as he headed the 
ball just inside the right post. 
</P>
<P>
	New England (8-10) didn't get its first shot until the 50th  
minute when Jamar Beasley was denied by Tom Prestus, who made a 
stop going low to his right to snuff Beasley's bid from 14 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	The match marked the league debut for 20-year-old United  
midfielder Chris Albright, who turned in a strong performance over 
his 77-minute debut. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
