<HEADLINE> Cuba's Pan Am Delegates Upset </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) -- Cuba's delegation to the Pan American  
Games claimed Sunday its athletes were being encouraged to defect 
by the Canadian media. 
</P>
<P>
	A Cuban athlete and a journalist have already defected, and Jose  
Ramon Fernandez, president of the Cuban Olympic Committee, said the 
delegation was ``very upset'' at the media. 
</P>
<P>
